ABUJA – A group, Nigerian Women for Bala Mohammed Nationwide, has vowed to mobilise other women in the 36 States and Federal Capital Territory to persuade Senator Bala Mohammed to run for president in 2023. National President of the group, Hon. Mary Ojochide Odoma, in a statement on Monday, said Governor Mohammed is the best man to succeed President Buhari. Odoma stated, “Mohammed has big ideas, charisma and all the needed leadership acumen to rescue Nigeria from its current state. Says Ortom Had No Hand In Selection Of Ochi’Idoma -CPS 2023: APC Working On One Lie That Will Return PDP To Power… She recalled that as FCT Minister, Senator Mohammed exhibited supreme intelligence, creativity and innovation, adding that his reforms are still being enjoyed in the capital city. Odoma said the group, drawn across party lines, will take time to visit some stakeholders like former Presidents Olusegun Obasanjo, General Abdulsalami Abubakar (rtd) and General Ibrahim Babangida (rtd). She added that they willl also meet Senator Iyorchia Ayu, Governor Nyesome Wike, Governor Samuel Ortom and other notable leaders within and outside the PDP to ensure that Senator Mohammed doesn’t only make himself available to run but gets the PDP ticket to win the presidential election in 2023. The women, therefore, urged Governor Mohammed to toss his hat into the ring to allow them properly mobilise.Bala, according to the women, has continued to set the pace, transforming Bauchi in terms of infrastructures and raising the standard of living of people of the state. If given the opportunity to lead Nigeria, Odoma believes Governor Mohammed’s impact will be instantly felt as he has garnered the requisite experience, exposure and expertise.